American rapper, Kanye West has finally released his long-awaited album titled ‘Jesus is King.’ He released the album on Friday and it has been trending on Twitter since then. Kanye’s wife, Kim Kardashian, celebrated the album’s release on Twitter. She tweeted, “Jesus Is King Is out!!!! Praise God 🙏🏼 What’s your favourite song?” READ ALSO: I’m now a Christian convert, Kanye West declares Some of the songs on the album include,’ Jesus is King’, ‘Use this Gospel,’ ‘God is,’ ‘Hands on’ and more. This is Kanye West’s ninth studio album and it is a total departure from his previous albums. There is not a single secular song on the album. Earlier this month, West announced that he had converted to Christianity and he had been holding Sunday services for some time now. See Kim’s tweet: 